so guys, you hear it on the news, in the magazines from your mom, "the number one new years resolution this year is fighting the battle of the bulge and we have some tips for losing those extra inches and gaining tons of self appreciation"
FUCKING BLAH you know actually how many people stay true to their new years resolution less than 10%, that is so sad, well this is what i am doing, and what i had planned to do since i found out my surgery was over Christmas break. my current weight is roughly 185 to 187 (depending on my mood) and my lowest weight was 165, i was so happy, i had a lot of confidence and i felt more attractive especially around Brandon, because i was proud of myself.
after my knee gets better, my goal is to reach my once lowest weight and i will be fine, but if i reach get to 170lbs i will still be happy, because i should! be motivated enough to lose those extra 5 pounds.
but, since i had had surgery it is easy to say i might have gained more fat while losing muscle mass so i don't quite know where i stand, i would just like to start back and lose as much as i can and i know i will do it as soon as my knee gets healed, i plan on starting soccer again, but regardless if i do or not i will lose my weight by any means necessary, healthily of-course, but i will do it.

another resolution is to have another great, happy, healthy year with my wonderful and compassionate boyfriend and i wish for many more to come.
i also want my grades to get better, usually i have problems with the first semester, getting back into the routine of things and i know that is a long time to bounce back but for some reason my second semester is the better one.

now the next step (which was planned today but my mother forgot it at Wal-mart) is to get a BRIGHT NEON color foam board such as pink, yellow, or lime green. i will write mt resolutions on it, and put it to the back of my door, so every morning i will see it and hopefully it will stick with me throughout the day. i want these things not too hard to do or ask for, but unlike those people who don't keep their resolution i want to be one of the few that does.

Your brain: 80% interpersonal, 200% visual, 60% verbal, and 60% mathematical!
Congratulations on being 400% smart! Actually, on my test, everyone is. The above score breaks down what kind of thinking you most enjoy doing. A score above 100% means you use that kind of thinking more than average, and a score below 100% means you use it less. It says nothing about how good you are at any one, just how interested you are in each, relatively. A substantial difference in scores between two people means, conclusively, that they are different kinds of thinkers.

Matching Summary: Each of us has different tastes. Still, I offer the following advice, which I think is obvious:

  1. Don't date someone if your interpersonal percentages differ by more than 80%.
  2. Don't be friends with someone if your verbal percentages differ by more than 100%.
  3. Don't have sex with someone if their math percentage is over 200%.



My test tracked 4 variables How you compared to other people your age and gender:
You scored higher than 55% on interpersonal
You scored higher than 94% on visual
You scored higher than 30% on verbal
You scored higher than 40% on mathematical
Link: The 4-Variable IQ Test written by chriscoyne on Ok Cupid

viruses in your body, viruses in your computer...viruses on your cell phone? what has all of this electronical advancement done to our once "perfect" electronical world? a virus (the cabir cell phone virus)is being spread arround the US from the philippines through bluetooth technology (technology that allows you to have wireless headsets) while using bluetooth you are at high risk for becoming infected with it(if someone arround you using bluetooth is also infected), this is going to affect over 70% of our population that has bluetooth ready phones that activly use it, such as stock brokers, lawyers, accountants ect. now i can understand having a virus on your computer, but pretty soon are we going to have norton antivirus for our phones? this is just becoming unbelievable. thank god that this is only transmitted through bluetooth and none have been created to attack through our internet ready phones. basically what this virus does is gets into your device that contracetd it and consumes battery life, it does not delete phone numbers (if a cell phone or PDA) or any kind of information, but instead of having 7 hours of talking time, you are limited to approximately three considering your "normal" talking time.
however, the virus is sent from one bluetooth phone to another, but on the recepients phone it will ask if you would like to recieve incoming bluetooth signal, now how many of you either accidently or purpously select yes because you dont think it would harm anything, i know i do. this is the leading cause of people contracting the virus, because they just select yes, no one thinks there is any harm, "oh whenever i put my wireless earbud close to my phone it asks me the same question, maybe my earbud got too far away from my phone, then regained signal, and is now asking me again if i would like to re-connect" again"
hopefully people will think, now that this is known throughout the US and maybe they will pay more attention to what is happening, and if you are one it is happening to,and you have this information, you more than likely wont get it. the story and links
